{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, the algorithms they compared were SAC, TD3, PPO, and Trust Region Policy Optimization (TRPO), evaluating energy savings, thermal stability, robustness, and data efficiency.",
    "Their results revealed the predominance of off-policy algorithms and, specifically, SAC, achieving consumption reductions of approximately 15% while guaranteeing comfort and data efficiency.",
    "Finally, the robustness was remarkable when the DRL algorithms were trained using different weather models, which increased their generalization and adaptability.",
    "Another remarkable and recent study is that of Brandi et al. (2022), where the control of an HVAC system based on the charging and discharging of a refrigerated storage facility is presented.",
    "In this case, two RBCs and an MPC controller were compared with two SAC implementations: one trained offline-in simulation, and the other one online-on the real building."
  ]
}